&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Education Support Officer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS PERMANENT.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for this vacancy in the Multi - professional Education Centre (MPEC) in the Princess of Wales Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the Medical Education Team, the post holder will provide local leadership and management support within the umbrella of Medical Education, with Team Leader responsibility for the local Education Centre and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The postholder will provide organisational, administrative, and project support to the Medical Education Centre Manager, specifically in relation to planning and delivery of the programme of Undergraduate/Postgraduate Medical Education in line with the requirements of the University Medical School(s) and Wales Deanery. This will require engagement with clinical divisions within the University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be educated to degree level, or have equivalent demonstrable experience, and will be required to demonstrate a working knowledge of NHS systems and structure, and the ability for leadership in a professional and sensitive manner at all times.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Leanne Holborn&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
